snippet: The Orioles have a solid rotation; entering the weekend, their five healthy starters each had an E.R.A. below 4.00 but above 3.50. But what Baltimore lacks is a proven No. 1 starter.
abstract: Extra Bases column; Baltimore Orioles have solid pitching rotation, with their five healthy starters each having an ERA below 4.00 but above 3.50; what they lack is a proven No 1, but in right-hander Kevin Gausman they might have a difference maker down the stretch; other baseball news noted.
lead_paragraph: The Orioles have a solid rotation; entering the weekend, their five healthy starters each had an E.R.A. below 4.00 but above 3.50. But what Baltimore lacks is a proven No. 1 starter.

headline.main: Orioles’ Strong Hand Has No Ace (Yet)
headline.print_headline: Orioles’ Strong Hand Has No Ace (Yet)
